Problem: Diagonal $W Y$ of square $W X Y Z$ has slope 2. Determine the sum of the slopes of $W X$ and $X Y$.
Since $W X$ and $X Y$ are perpendicular, the product of their slopes is $-1$. Let the slope of $W X$ be $m$. Then the slope of $X Y$ is $-1/m$. Since the slope of $W Y$ is $2$, we have
\begin{align*} \frac{-1/m}{m} &amp;= 2 \\ \Rightarrow\qquad -\frac{1}{m^2} &amp;= 2 \\ \Rightarrow\qquad m^2 &amp;= -\frac{1}{2} \\ \Rightarrow\qquad m &amp;= \pm \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \end{align*}
